Key Match Events: David Warner and Travis Head blitzed 70 runs in the first five overs
Adam Zampa dismissed both England openers inside his first 11 balls
England managed only 92 for 6 in the following 13 overs
Zampa made the difference, dismissing Phil Salt and Jos Buttler
Australia reached 200 with regular boundaries at the back end
Post-Match Reflections: England has one point from their first two matches and faces an anxious week ahead in Antigua
They will almost certainly need to beat both Oman and Namibia, but even then would likely have to rely on net run rate to qualify for the second round ahead of Scotland
Miscellaneous Highlights: One square boundary was nine metres shorter than the other, measured at just 58m
England opened the bowling with spin from both ends
Will Jacks, surprisingly given the second over, conceded three sixes in his first four balls
Mark Wood's first over from the same end also cost 22
